<p>Here are some notes for getting started and quick reference when using my new VX-8GR.  Notation is defined at the end of this page.</p>

<p>#Yaesu VX-8GR Set Up for APRS Beaconing</p>

<ul>
  <li>Note: Circle with dot in upper left, on Station List indicates that beaconing is active.</li>
  <li>Enable GPS ++</li>
  <li>Set call sign, SSID, icon (One time, when new.) ++</li>
  <li>Enable APRS modem ++</li>
  <li>Enter APRS (144.390) into the <strong>B</strong> frequency:
    <ul>
      <li>Tap &lt;Bv&gt; to select the B-band.</li>
      <li>Use the digit keypad to enter 144.390</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Enable Beaconing:
    <ul>
      <li>Access APRS Settings Menu ++</li>
      <li>&lt;turn&gt; to 14: BEA- CON TX.</li>
      <li>Tap menu</li>
      <li>&lt;turn&gt; to Auto</li>
      <li>Tap menu</li>
      <li>
        <turn> to 12: BEACON INTERVAL.
</turn>
      </li>
      <li>Tap menu</li>
      <li>&lt;turn&gt; to select interval</li>
      <li>Tap &lt;PTT&gt; to save</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<p>#Enable APRS Modem</p>
<ul>
  <li>Access APRS Settings Menu ++</li>
  <li>Turn to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">3 APRS MODEM</code>.</li>
  <li>Tap &lt;menu&gt;.</li>
  <li>Turn to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">1200bps</code>.</li>
  <li>Tap &lt;PTT&gt; to save.</li>
</ul>

<p>#Enable GPS</p>

<ul>
  <li>Tap &lt;menu&gt; until GPRS screen.</li>
  <li>Hold &lt;menu&gt;.</li>
  <li>Turn to select <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">18 GPS Power</code></li>
  <li>Turn to toggle On/Off</li>
  <li>Tap &lt;PTT&gt; to save On/Off</li>
  <li>Note: &lt;mode&gt; toggles North-up/Heading-up.  White arrow = heading-up; black arrow = north-up.</li>
  <li>Tap &lt;menu&gt; to return to non-GPS mode.</li>
</ul>

<p>#Set call sign, SSID, icon:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Access APRS Settings Menu ++</li>
  <li>Turn to select <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">22 My Call Sign</code>.</li>
  <li>Tap &lt;menu&gt;.</li>
  <li>Tap &lt;mode&gt; until pointer is in 7th call sign column.</li>
  <li>Turn to select SSID <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">-7</code> (unless you used -7 on other HT).</li>
  <li>Tap &lt;menu&gt;.</li>
  <li>Turn to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">24 My Symbol</code>.</li>
  <li>Tap &lt;menu&gt;.</li>
  <li>Turn to select running man.</li>
  <li>Tap &lt;menu&gt;.</li>
  <li>Turn to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">23 My Position</code>.</li>
  <li>Tap &lt;menu&gt;.</li>
  <li>Turn to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">GPS</code>.</li>
  <li>Tap &lt;menu&gt;.</li>
</ul>

<p>#How to Use the Keypad</p>
<ul>
  <li>Multi-press the digit keys as you do on a cell phone, to cycle through the characters assigned to that digit.</li>
  <li>Special characters:
    <ul>
      <li></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>&lt;Band&gt; is cursor-left</li>
  <li>&lt;Mode&gt; is cursor-right</li>
  <li>&lt;Hm/Rv&gt; appears to be select (and it stands for Home/Reverse)</li>
  <li>To append an SSID to a destination address, complete entry of the base call sign and then rotate.</li>
  <li>Lock/unlock = tap Power.  Lock icon in bottom center shows lock status.</li>
  <li>V/M is the Delete key (sometimes)</li>
  <li>To enter â€œ@â€, press 1 and rotate clockwise 15. (It is right after â€œ?â€.)
    <ul>
      <li>Or press 0 six times for â€œ?â€ and rotate clockwise 1.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>To enter â€œ.â€, press 0 eight times or press 0 and rotate counter-clockwise 2.</li>
  <li>Space is 00.</li>
</ul>

<p>#Access APRS Settings Menu</p>
<ul>
  <li>Tap &lt;menu&gt; until <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Station List</code>.</li>
  <li>Hold &lt;menu&gt;.</li>
</ul>

<p>#Send APRS Message</p>
<ul>
  <li>Tap &lt;menu&gt; until <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">APRS MESSAGE</code></li>
  <li>&lt;Hm/Rv&gt;</li>
  <li>Enter call-sign-with-SSID (destination)</li>
  <li>&lt;mode&gt;</li>
  <li>Enter msg up to 67 char</li>
  <li>Press TX/PO (the â€˜atomâ€™ key)</li>
  <li>The radio tries 5x, one per minute.  IF it gets an ACK, it puts an asterisk after the â€œTXâ€ in the message display.  Otherwise, it displays the remaining attempt count, or a period if it timed out.</li>
  <li>To erase the current message buffer (to send a NEW message):
    <ul>
      <li>&lt;Band&gt;</li>
      <li>A/B to select CLEAR</li>
      <li>&lt;V/M&gt;</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<p>#Delete APRS Message</p>
<ul>
  <li>Select the message</li>
  <li>Press &lt;V/M&gt;</li>
</ul>

<p>#Yaesu VX-8GR Cheat Sheet</p>

<ul>
  <li>Volume - Hold_Vol + Turn_knob</li>
  <li>Squelch - FW, Mon, Turn_knob, FW, Mon</li>
  <li>MONI/T.Call = Suppress squelch</li>
  <li>F/W = Alt (i.e. access the <em>other</em> function of the keypad)</li>
  <li>Change transmit power = F/W + Atom</li>
  <li>Check power level = L1/L2/L3/Hi in the lower-left on the display</li>
</ul>

<hr />
<p>Notes:</p>

<ul>
  <li>â€œTapâ€ means a brief button press.</li>
  <li>â€œHoldâ€ means to hold the button about 1 second, until its secondary function activates.</li>
  <li>â€œTurnâ€ means to turn the only knob on the radio.  (Since the knob is the only thing that turns, I donâ€™t say â€œTurn <em>knob</em>.â€</li>
  <li>â€++â€ means to see procedure defined elsewhere on this page.</li>
  <li>â€œx+yâ€ means â€œat same timeâ€; â€œx,yâ€ means â€œsequentiallyâ€</li>
  <li>Thereâ€™s a key in the lower left, with TX/PO as its alternate function, that looks like an atom with revolving electrons to me.  I call this the â€˜atomâ€™ key.</li>
  <li>BEEP-BEEP: If you press the atom key and it goes beep-beep, check to be sure the radio isnâ€™t locked to frequency 1. If it is, hold â€œBâ€ until it goes back to 2-frequency mode with 144.390 as the B frequency.</li>
</ul>

